WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:09.279
Praise the Lord. Let's start. We waited for a little bit for you all to come on before I start talking, but thank you for joining us.

00:00:09.280 --> 00:00:14.798
Good morning, family. Good evening, wherever you are all around the world.

00:00:14.799 --> 00:00:18.034
Thank you for joining us again today; we really appreciate it.

00:00:18.035 --> 00:00:25.358
We're going to pray, and we'll just go tubing tonight and talk about some of the things that we're seeing in the news.

00:00:25.359 --> 00:00:34.639
I'll go over some of the things the Lord said to me today when I was driving around.

00:00:34.640 --> 00:00:47.822
He talked to me about William Seymour and the box that he used to place on his head before every single meeting.

00:00:47.823 --> 00:01:01.998
He would sit in the corner of the room with the box on his head for sometimes up to an hour, sometimes less, depending on how long the Lord told him to do it.

00:01:01.999 --> 00:01:07.438
The Lord said to me, 'Brandon, my people must find their box.

00:01:07.439 --> 00:01:16.399
You must find your box.'What is your box? That's what he started talking to me about.

00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:25.359
I said, 'Well, what do you mean?'He said, 'I will not share my glory with anybody for what's about to take place in this last outpouring.

00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:45.687
I will not share my glory with anybody.'William Seymour, before the service would start and the glory would start, would find that place of death to himself: humility, humbling yourself underneath the mighty hand of the Lord.

00:01:45.688 --> 00:02:07.679
So he started talking to me about putting the box on. He said, 'Brandon, I'm not going to tell you what the box is for you; you'll have to figure it out yourself.'But a box is not just lip service, telling people that it is not you concerning the glory; it's a heart thing.

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:28.479
He said, 'I'm looking at the heart—not just what words say.'There are so many preachers, he said, who get on the stage and say, 'We give you all the glory, we give you all the honor, and we give you all the praise,'but their heart is all about themselves and they don't have the box on their head.

00:02:28.480 --> 00:02:40.479
He said, 'The bigger the box, the more freedom I will give you. The larger the box, it's like being in a refrigerator box.

00:02:40.480 --> 00:02:44.810
You have a lot more room to move around in there; there's a lot more space to do things.

00:02:44.811 --> 00:03:13.318
But the smaller the box, the less the trust, as you must always deflect to give him the glory for what's about to take place.'He talked to me about Sister Kuhlman, Kathryn Kuhlman, and how she would always give him the glory, but it was always from the heart.

00:03:13.319 --> 00:03:29.980
The moment people started to try to uplift her or tell her how great she was, she would recluse because she realized the source of the power and the source of the glory was him.

00:03:29.981 --> 00:03:37.752
As long as the glory is manifesting through you, you're a container, you're a vessel.

00:03:37.753 --> 00:03:49.239
He's moving through you, but it's always to deflect to him. The box represents dying to self.

00:03:49.240 --> 00:04:02.399
The Apostle Paul said, 'I die daily.'The Lord started saying that to die daily is a place of humility.

00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:09.402
It's not something that you have to convince yourself of. No, you die daily.

00:04:09.403 --> 00:04:20.638
The more I use you and the greater the glory on your life, the more you have to find the box to deflect.

00:04:20.639 --> 00:04:30.635
The more you're accurate and the more things come to pass in the days ahead, you're always to deflect.

00:04:30.636 --> 00:04:41.758
I always go back to it—and I do it for myself because it's really true—I'm just the janitor, which I was just a couple of years ago.

00:04:41.759 --> 00:05:04.088
No matter if the president, a senator, or the head of whatever country is watching your channel and they get their information and use it, it's not mine; it's the Lord's.

00:05:04.089 --> 00:05:11.620
The Lord was really telling me what's about to take place in the days ahead with the church.

00:05:11.621 --> 00:05:19.439
He said, 'You're about to see something that you've never seen before, and there's nothing to compare it to.

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:36.239
You're about to see something that you've always longed for, what the elders always longed for, but there's really nothing to compare it to. For I'm going to do something unusual, son.

00:05:36.240 --> 00:06:01.198
It will be something that we've never seen, and I'm not a cookie-cutter.'There are so many times we come on here and take communion and have a pattern, and I tell you things that the Lord is showing us, but the Holy Spirit has free reign to do whatever he wants to do.

00:06:01.199 --> 00:06:15.671
He used a word that I didn't even know the meaning of. What was the word? Status quo? No, no, no. Ask your mother.

00:06:15.672 --> 00:06:24.994
He used a word and said, 'Don't ever do this.'I said, 'What does that even mean?'So Diana had to look it up.

00:06:24.995 --> 00:06:42.799
As we were being instructed by the Holy Spirit today, I thought, 'What's your box?'Anomaly.

00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:48.399
Don't become an anomaly. There are so many people that have become an anomaly.

00:06:48.400 --> 00:06:58.700
I didn't even know what an anomaly was, but whenever he uses big words like that, it goes with everything he's been saying.

00:06:58.701 --> 00:07:11.808
But I want you to know we must find the box. The greater the glory and the greater the platform, the greater the death.

00:07:11.809 --> 00:07:20.067
He said that the light afflictions bring forth the greater glory.

00:07:20.067 --> 00:07:29.679
This refining—we have this treasure in earthen vessels so that the excellency of the power is known of him and not of us.

00:07:29.680 --> 00:07:43.670
It's more than you'll ever know—that to sustain what God has called us to do in these last days is to continually give him the glory for what he's doing.

00:07:43.671 --> 00:07:56.875
Regardless, because of insecurity and because people deal with flesh—our flesh likes praise just like the devil; he wanted praise in heaven.

00:07:56.876 --> 00:08:04.079
He said, 'I'll exalt myself above the Lord,'and boy, did he sure mess up.

00:08:04.080 --> 00:08:17.597
But our flesh always cries out for more because maybe you were the kid the bully in the schoolyard was always picking on or the last pick at sports.

00:08:17.598 --> 00:08:35.537
It's always nice for somebody to say, 'Well done, you did a good job.'But the Lord was showing me that for what is coming, there are so many of you who watch this channel and are excited about this end-time outpouring.

00:08:35.538 --> 00:08:48.944
I have this revival behind me right now because one of the greatest moves of God this world has ever seen is about to hit from shore to shore, all around this world.

00:08:48.945 --> 00:08:58.818
He'll choose individual people—the new Davids, the new Esthers, and the new leaders of this generation—to take the baton and run and bring in the greatest harvest.

00:08:58.819 --> 00:09:16.876
But the Lord told me, 'I want you to tell my people: find your box like William Seymour.'It doesn't have to be a physical box, but what's your box?

00:09:16.877 --> 00:09:25.278
William Seymour's was a real box, and he put that crate on his head.

00:09:25.279 --> 00:09:37.155
But he said, 'What's your box?'It's the place of surrender, the place of death, the place to humble yourself underneath the mighty hand of the Lord.

00:09:37.156 --> 00:09:50.032
We have the treasure in earthen vessels so that the excellency of the power will be known of him. He will not share his glory with any of us.

00:09:50.033 --> 00:10:10.559
Regardless of how amazing things are with the words and things that happen in the days ahead, I always want you to know that Brandon Biggs is just a servant of the Most High God, just like you are.

00:10:10.560 --> 00:10:21.119
It's so important that you stay the janitor in your eyes. Don't lose sight of yourself.

00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:26.879
The Lord always says to stay grounded. Keep your feet on the ground.

00:10:26.880 --> 00:10:38.719
Remember, even today, put your feet on the ground. I was driving and I said, 'What does that mean?'Ground yourself.

00:10:38.720 --> 00:10:49.759
Look inside. Go deep within. This is nothing compared to what I want to do in the days ahead with you.

00:10:49.760 --> 00:10:59.838
This is nothing compared to what I want to do with me and each one of these individuals that are here praying with you.

00:10:59.839 --> 00:11:09.288
There are so many souls that are about to come into the kingdom of God, and there's so much arrogance and so much pride behind the pulpits.

00:11:09.289 --> 00:11:16.611
The Lord said, 'Brandon, I'm going to humble the church. There's going to be a cleansing. There's going to be a 1 Corinthians 5:5 moment.

00:11:16.612 --> 00:11:29.518
You're going to see these things in the days ahead.'And the young Davids, the new voices that I have for this hour will rise up and they will take the baton from the elders.

00:11:29.519 --> 00:11:34.420
There'll be new Esthers. There'll be these new voices that seemingly came out of nowhere.

00:11:34.421 --> 00:11:44.159
He said, 'I will use them greatly in the days ahead.'But you've not even entered into the second phase of what I've called you to do yet.

00:11:44.160 --> 00:11:53.902
Signs and wonders will follow them that believe. He said, 'I don't want you to do videos so much until I tell you to.

00:11:53.903 --> 00:11:58.879
I want you to be more strategic in the way you do things in prayer.

00:11:58.880 --> 00:12:07.565
Do it this way and do it exactly.'He's given me great instruction for us to pray together and how we are supposed to function as an army.

00:12:07.566 --> 00:12:14.958
As we flow in the army, as we flow with the anointing of the Holy Ghost, we will have great results.

00:12:14.959 --> 00:12:30.424
With great power comes great responsibility. They stole that from the Lord, I guarantee you.

00:12:30.425 --> 00:12:44.961
I always want to tell you all this because it's very important that you understand he is a good God and he loves you, but he'll not share his glory with anybody.

00:12:44.962 --> 00:13:07.039
Many of you have major calls on your life, and it's so interesting because so many of you email saying, 'I had this vision'or 'I had this dream.'You have so much potential, but you're not dead to yourself.

00:13:07.040 --> 00:13:28.159
There's so much ego and so much stuff going on. I said, 'Find the janitor.'No matter how much you feel that you should have a platform or wonder why God is not using you yet, find the place of death. Find the janitor.

00:13:28.160 --> 00:13:47.774
You might say, 'I'm a cleaner now, I do this and that,'but the Lord said, 'Find the janitor and die there to yourself.'I don't know how else to describe that to you; you have to figure it out yourself.

00:13:47.775 --> 00:13:57.113
The more you squirm, it's like someone who lays a sacrifice on the altar to the Father.

00:13:57.114 --> 00:14:03.706
My life is for His. You're up there and He's looking to see if you're dead.

00:14:03.707 --> 00:14:17.599
You say, 'I'm dead,'but the Lord looks and says, 'No, you're not dead yet.'You keep saying, 'I'm dead,'but you're just looking around like a kid playing.

00:14:17.600 --> 00:14:22.873
When you're truly dead, you'll know it. There's no pretending.

00:14:22.874 --> 00:14:47.198
Dead is dead, and the flesh starts to stink. You'll know it. It's a place of surrender.

00:14:47.199 --> 00:15:18.660
It's a place of saying, 'Father, I'm not going to complain about what you have for me anymore, no matter if this whole thing goes away tomorrow.'Between all the invitations I get to preach from all around the globe—some in Australia and South America—the Australian one was tempting because it would be fun to go way down under and see what's down there.

00:15:18.661 --> 00:15:43.838
But I won't do it until the Lord says. It's interesting because I told Diana that the more everything takes place, the more I just want to be reclusive.

00:15:43.839 --> 00:15:58.773
Change happens so quickly for all of us. The Lord will put his finger on you, and the moment he does, he says, 'Brandon, I don't want anyone to get the glory for what I'm about to do in your life.

00:15:58.774 --> 00:16:03.566
There's no platform that will ever be given to you. It'll all be by my hand.

00:16:03.567 --> 00:16:13.679
The money I bless you with, the notoriety, everything will come from me.

00:16:13.680 --> 00:16:25.328
Just bring in my harvest.'All that to say this: Braden has some of these clips and he'll show you this, and we'll go right into tubing.

00:16:25.329 --> 00:16:33.039
That's really what He's been talking to me about the last couple of days. He gave me a scripture.

00:16:33.040 --> 00:16:57.750
I was watching Sister Kuhlman and she said her main thing with the Lord is Psalm 17:8: 'Keep me as the apple of thy eye.

00:16:57.751 --> 00:17:11.494
Hide me under the shadow of thy wings.'Her description of that in this sermon—and we can put the link below—is amazing.

00:17:11.495 --> 00:17:15.371
Braden, I'll send this to you so you can show them this sermon.

00:17:15.372 --> 00:17:27.942
I would encourage everybody to listen to it. This guy has a YouTube channel with 3,000 subscribers.

00:17:27.943 --> 00:17:48.912
Diana found it. Someone left him an attic full of Mrs. Kuhlman's tapes, reel-to-reels, and old stuff that has never been public.

00:17:48.913 --> 00:18:06.850
There are recordings of someone in the audience in Ohio recording her.

00:18:06.851 --> 00:18:18.340
He's bringing forth all this lost material, and these archives are life-changing.

00:18:18.341 --> 00:18:28.399
He has hundreds of boxes from a fan of Kathryn Kuhlman who just stored it in the attic.

00:18:28.400 --> 00:18:46.515
Diana and I feel like we're at a buffet. I'm going to give this to you.

00:18:46.516 --> 00:18:53.838
I don't even think he knows who I am, but I watch his channel. It's not about him; it's about Katherine.

00:18:53.839 --> 00:19:19.801
I'll give you one sermon that is amazing; the scripture is 'The secret to success is loving Him.'This is how I keep myself full.

00:19:19.802 --> 00:19:24.841
I'm a scavenger; I pick the bone until there's nothing left.

00:19:24.842 --> 00:19:45.894
I told Diana we do this every year. Do you have that for them? Can you put it on there so they can see it?

00:19:45.895 --> 00:19:58.342
I want them to grasp it because this will change your life if you listen.

00:19:58.343 --> 00:20:08.879
People ask me about these books; there it is: Oral Roberts, 1972.

00:20:08.880 --> 00:20:21.839
Isn't that awesome? Kenneth Hagin books. Things that will change your life. I don't know what his channel's name is.

00:20:21.840 --> 00:20:30.649
Kathryn Kuhlman Radio, no AI, because there's so many people trying to make fake AI sermons.

00:20:30.650 --> 00:20:36.765
And this is all her original archives of stuff that this guy stored up, so it will bless you.

00:20:36.766 --> 00:20:43.356
It's trying to help. If you want to listen to it, fine; if you don't, fine. But there you go.

00:20:43.357 --> 00:20:57.266
When Diana found this, I went, "Oh my goodness, this blessed me so."I'll play a second of it so they can hear it. I'll be right back.

00:20:57.267 --> 00:21:13.359
I dare say that practically every young person who is graduating today—every one of you young people who are wearing a cap and a gown—has come from a Christian home.

00:21:13.360 --> 00:21:26.079
If you've not come from a Christian home, you've had the finest Christian training here at Oral Roberts University. You know doctrine, you know your Bible.

00:21:26.080 --> 00:21:46.158
And for me to stand up here and preach a message, for me to give you doctrine, would be so foolish, for nothing that I could say to you would be something you have not already heard and known.

00:21:46.159 --> 00:22:21.839
I just want to take the lid off of my heart for a few minutes. Two weeks ago, I was in a music hall in Kansas City, Missouri, and I got up early one morning and I drove 60 miles out of Kansas City to Concordia, Missouri, where I was born.

00:22:21.840 --> 00:22:40.719
And I did something: I went back to that little Methodist church, and I was so shocked that it got so small in such a short time.

00:22:40.720 --> 00:22:53.999
When I was young, it looked so big. When I went back two weeks ago, the same pews were there.

00:22:54.000 --> 00:23:04.719
They were just as shiny as the Sunday morning when I was 14 years of age and received that wonderful spiritual experience of being born again.

00:23:04.720 --> 00:23:23.279
Walking into the vestibule, the rope was still there. A little tiny Methodist church, not seating any more than a hundred people—you could maybe squeeze 125 people in the church.

00:23:23.280 --> 00:23:39.366
Walking into that little vestibule, there was the rope that always rang the bell when somebody died in Concordia.

00:23:39.367 --> 00:23:53.279
If it was a young person, they tolled it once. When it was a middle-aged person, they would toll the bell twice.

00:23:53.280 --> 00:24:06.239
If it was an elderly person, they would toll it three times. And then everybody ran to the telephone and asked the one telephone operator who died.

00:24:06.240 --> 00:24:18.639
And the bell was still there and the rope was still there that had tolled for so many people.

00:24:18.640 --> 00:24:32.019
And I walked in and I sat in the corner of the same pew, the third row from the front.

00:24:32.020 --> 00:24:46.158
I sat in that same corner of that pew that I sat that Sunday morning when I was only 14 years of age.

00:24:46.159 --> 00:24:50.639
It was the very first time that I had ever felt the power of the Holy Spirit.

00:24:50.640 --> 00:24:55.399
And I didn't recognize the power of the Holy Spirit—believe me, I knew nothing about the Holy Spirit.

00:24:55.400 --> 00:25:05.278
I knew nothing whatsoever about the third person of the Trinity. Nothing.

00:25:05.279 --> 00:25:09.717
I don't even remember who the preacher was; I don't remember one thing that he said.

00:25:09.718 --> 00:25:14.020
I've never seen anyone accept Christ as their Savior in that Methodist church.

00:25:14.021 --> 00:25:21.199
I'm not sure that anyone was converted before or since. I'm not sure.

00:25:21.200 --> 00:25:29.787
But suddenly, as they were singing the last hymn and I had the Methodist hymnal in my hand, I began to shake.

00:25:29.788 --> 00:25:42.239
It was years later that I recognized it as the power of the Holy Spirit, and I began to shake so much that I laid the hymnal down and then I knew that I had to do something.

00:25:42.240 --> 00:25:55.128
I did the only thing that I knew to do: I slipped out from that pew and sat down on the front row, on the front pew.

00:25:55.129 --> 00:26:07.519
And nobody knew what to do with me. The preacher didn't know, and I cried. What a joy.

00:26:07.520 --> 00:26:15.999
One of the old sisters came to me and said, "Oh, Kathryn, don't cry."I didn't have a hanky, I remember that, and my tears were running, my nose was running.

00:26:16.000 --> 00:26:36.558
And she gave me a handkerchief and she said, "Oh, Kathryn, you've been such a good girl all your life, don't cry."And both of us knew she was lying, because those things didn't happen in Concordia; I made them happen.

00:26:36.559 --> 00:26:48.798
That marvelous experience of being born again, that glorious experience.

00:26:48.799 --> 00:27:10.879
So help me, there's never been a moment since that experience—that Sunday morning in that little Methodist church in that front pew when I was born again—there's never been a split second that I've ever doubted my salvation.

00:27:10.880 --> 00:27:16.665
And sitting there two weeks ago in that same pew, I relived many things.

00:27:16.666 --> 00:27:29.199
I remember as a little girl standing there, and the only time Papa ever went to church—he would never go to church; my Papa hated preachers.

00:27:29.200 --> 00:27:41.278
If he saw the preacher coming down the street, and if he saw the preacher before the preacher saw him, the preacher never saw him.

00:27:41.279 --> 00:27:59.278
He went to church only at Christmas time when his girl would give a recitation on Children's Day when she sang a song.

00:27:59.279 --> 00:28:09.439
They always said that Kathryn was the apple of her Papa's eye.

00:28:09.440 --> 00:28:45.439
I've heard that ever since I was a little girl: "You know, Kathryn, that mean little girl with the freckled face and the red hair is the apple of her Papa's eye."And I knew it, and it was my security.

00:28:45.440 --> 00:29:13.199
I knew it. And every time I got up to give that recitation, I saw only one person in that little church, and that was Papa. And I did my best for Papa; I was the apple of his eye.

00:29:13.200 --> 00:29:39.918
And sitting there two weeks ago in that same pew, three rows from the front, where the Holy Spirit first spoke to my heart, I sat there in silence and it seemed like all the years of my life came before me.

00:29:39.919 --> 00:29:49.918
There were the turkey houses where I slept when I first started out.

00:29:49.919 --> 00:30:03.918
I slept in a straw stack once. I lived on butter horns for a week—that was all I could afford.

00:30:03.919 --> 00:30:18.479
There have been deep waters, very deep waters. The sun hasn't always shone.

00:30:18.480 --> 00:30:40.879
And I sat there and I thought, "What through all of these years really has been the motivating force in this life of mine?"I wasn't made to do what I've done all my life.

00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:49.354
There wasn't enough money in the whole world to pay me for the long hours and the sleepless nights.

00:30:49.355 --> 00:31:09.759
Believe me, I tell you the truth, there's not enough money in the world to pay me for the way I've worked in my lifetime.

00:31:09.760 --> 00:31:23.359
Nobody forced me to do it. It wasn't because of doctrine; it wasn't because I was afraid of God.

00:31:23.360 --> 00:31:32.719
I didn't do it because I feared God—I'm not that kind of a person.

00:31:32.720 --> 00:31:51.038
I'm just not that kind of a person. I didn't do it because somebody told me to do it.

00:31:51.039 --> 00:32:15.759
I've had one verse of scripture that I've wept over; I've held it closely to me, and it's been the motivating force of my life.

00:32:15.760 --> 00:32:57.599
I read it to you: "Keep me as the apple of the eye; hide me under thy wings."A million times I've held this precious word to my heart.

00:32:57.600 --> 00:33:07.439
I knew the security that there was in being the apple of Papa's eye.

00:33:07.440 --> 00:33:13.439
I never feared his wrath. Papa never laid a hand on me. Never.

00:33:13.440 --> 00:33:22.798
Not that I didn't need it, but he didn't do it. My Papa never laid a hand on me.

00:33:22.799 --> 00:33:27.148
All Papa had to do was just look at me a certain way—that's all.

00:33:27.149 --> 00:33:39.518
He would get just a certain look on his face, and I knew it was a look of disapproval.

00:33:39.519 --> 00:34:05.518
And I loved him so much. I was the apple of his eye, and I wasn't going to let him down.

00:34:05.519 --> 00:34:30.183
A million times, methinks, I've held this close to my heart and I said, "Wonderful Jesus, more than anything else in the whole world, I want to be the apple of your eye."I have but one ambition in life—just one, only one.

00:34:30.184 --> 00:35:17.439
I live for one thing and one thing only—just one thing. Just one thing I desire, but one thing above everything else in the world: to be the apple of your eye.

00:35:17.440 --> 00:35:35.519
I want your smile. It's beautiful. It blesses me so. I think I've listened to that, I can't tell you how many times, going over and over and just thinking about what she's saying.

00:35:35.520 --> 00:35:59.759
And you look at somebody who walked with Him the way she did in a modern age, you know, and that's why my friend Billy Burke was mentored by her, and thank God he's been a friend to me, because it's cross-pollination.

00:35:59.760 --> 00:36:07.838
There's so much about cross-pollination. You can feel it; it changes you.

00:36:07.839 --> 00:36:13.422
And I know it's all the Holy Spirit, and He changes you from the inside out by the Word of God.

00:36:13.423 --> 00:36:26.812
But there is a lot about cross-pollination when you get around people that have been around it, the presence changes you.

00:36:26.813 --> 00:36:29.825
You get around people. It's like, who are you hanging around?

00:36:29.826 --> 00:36:46.319
I used to see all the time, "Who are you hanging around?"I'll tell you where you'll be in the next couple of years by who you're hanging around, what books you're reading, what you're watching on TV, and what you're meditating on.

00:36:46.320 --> 00:37:02.907
You must come up higher in your walk with the Father in 2026. But I bring all this to you because it's what has helped me, and so people are always asking.

00:37:02.908 --> 00:37:11.964
So, I just try to put you in the direction of... and I had somebody email me and said, "Brandon, you can't talk about finances.

00:37:11.965 --> 00:37:18.779
You shouldn't do that."Listen, I tell you what I hear. I'm not a financial adviser.

00:37:18.780 --> 00:37:29.786
